<br>
a) Excited that they got into a beta test.<br>
<br>
b) Upset that they <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>didn't</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> get into a beta test.<br>
<br>
To those of you who fit either category... why do you even care?<br>
<br>
Some people want a chance to test-run a game they're interested in... but the game you're testing during beta is usually only half-baked, and will probably launch half-baked as well, approaching &quot;cooked&quot; a few months &amp; patches after release.  Why sour yourself on a game you were interested in by playing when it's not ready?<br>
<br>
Some people see it as a status symbol I guess, showing that they were able to sucessfully camp a beta registration page or something.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I've beta tested a couple games myself, and found that the game was always much more fun at launch than it was during beta.  I thought doing the beta test would be a great way to help find game-killing bugs that the dev team would fix prior to launch, but after discovering that they pretty much ignore all beta tester feedback throughout the whole process unless it's a huge mass-petition or something I've given up on that daydream <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I suppose to some extent beta testing is good for powergamers, cuz you're given access to content that your &quot;competitors&quot; can't see yet, and thus you hit the ground running when the game is launched.  I gave up defining my fun by comparing my success to others a long time ago though so that's not for me.<br>
<br>
So anyways, I guess this post is mainly for the people upset that the Stormhammer server players get first shot at EQ2 Beta, to whom I ask... who gives a crap?  Beta testing suxxors  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
